---
import DocsLayout from '../../../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../../../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import Callout from '../../../../../components/Callout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Remaining tickets" description="Work through the rest of the backlog independently.">
  <h1 class="mb-6">Remaining Tickets</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">You know the loop now: direct → verify → review → merge. Work through the remaining tickets in the backlog using the same cycle for each one.</p>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">The key shift from here: you're working independently. You have the backlog with acceptance criteria for every ticket. You have the design spec to check against. You have the loop. Use them.</p>

  <h2 class="mb-4">The rhythm</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-2">For each ticket:</p>
  <div class="space-y-3 mb-8">
    <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
      <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">1</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary"><strong class="text-text">Direct:</strong> Tell Claude <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">Start Ticket N.</code></p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
      <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">2</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary"><strong class="text-text">Verify:</strong> Check every acceptance criterion. Open the browser. Use DevTools. Compare to the design spec.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
      <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">3</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary"><strong class="text-text">Review:</strong> Read Claude's self-review and Gemini's review on the PR.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
      <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">4</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary"><strong class="text-text">Decide:</strong> Merge it or tell Claude exactly what to fix.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="mb-4">What to watch for</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">As you move through tickets, different types of work require different verification approaches:</p>

  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
    <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr class="bg-bg-muted">
          <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-semibold border-b border-border">Ticket type</th>
          <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-semibold border-b border-border">How to verify</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr class="border-b border-border">
          <td class="px-4 py-3">Layout & navigation</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-secondary">Resize the browser. Test mobile. Click every link. Check sticky elements by scrolling.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border bg-bg-subtle">
          <td class="px-4 py-3">Visual sections</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-secondary">Compare to the design spec. Use DevTools to check fonts, colours, spacing. Don't eyeball — measure.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border">
          <td class="px-4 py-3">Content sections</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-secondary">Count items — does the number match the PRD? Check that content comes from the data source, not hardcoded in components.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border bg-bg-subtle">
          <td class="px-4 py-3">SEO & meta</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-secondary">View Page Source. Search for meta tags. Run Lighthouse. These are invisible — you can't check by looking at the page.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border">
          <td class="px-4 py-3">Deploy</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-secondary">Check the live URL. Test on your actual phone. Run Lighthouse on the production URL, not localhost.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <Callout variant="warning">
    <p class="text-sm"><strong>Anti-scope check:</strong> After every ticket, ask yourself: "Did Claude add anything that isn't in the backlog or PRD?" AI tends to add features, polish, and "improvements" that were never asked for. Catching this is one of the most important directing skills. If you find something that wasn't specified, tell Claude to remove it.</p>
  </Callout>

  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-10">When something goes wrong</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">It will. That's part of the process. Here's how to handle common situations:</p>

  <details class="mb-3 border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <summary>A criterion fails</summary>
    <div class="p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Be specific: "The criterion says [exact criterion]. What I see is [exact observation]. Fix this." Don't say "it's broken" — describe the gap between expectation and reality.</p>
    </div>
  </details>
  <details class="mb-3 border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <summary>Claude broke something that worked before</summary>
    <div class="p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Tell Claude: "After merging this ticket, [describe what broke]. This was working before. Fix the regression without changing the new work." Regressions happen — catching them is the Director's job.</p>
    </div>
  </details>
  <details class="mb-3 border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <summary>The review flagged something you don't understand</summary>
    <div class="p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Ask Claude: "Gemini said [paste comment]. Explain what this means and whether it matters for this project." Not every review comment is actionable — developing judgment about which ones matter is part of the learning.</p>
    </div>
  </details>
  <details class="mb-3 border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <summary>You're stuck and don't know what to check</summary>
    <div class="p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Go back to the backlog. Read the acceptance criteria line by line. For each one, write down pass or fail. If you can't check a criterion, ask Claude how to verify it.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <Callout variant="info">
    <p class="text-sm"><strong>DevTools tip:</strong> Right-click any element → Inspect. The Styles panel shows CSS properties. The Computed panel shows final calculated values. The box model diagram shows margin and padding. You'll use this constantly for visual verification.</p>
  </Callout>

  <p class="text-text-secondary mt-8">Once all frontend tickets are done, move on to <a href="/web-dev/projects/1/testing">testing</a>.</p>
</DocsLayout>
